1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:02,600
"超感神探" 前情提要...
Previously on "the mentalist"...

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:05,560
Van Pelt在Bertram的办公室发现了加密文件
Van Pelt found some coded files in Bertram's office.

3
00:00:05,560 --> 00:00:07,200
像个名单
It looks like a list.

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,260
- 我叫Patrick - 我叫Kim
- Patrick.  - Kim.

5
00:00:09,260 --> 00:00:12,930
- 谢谢你 我需要陪伴  - 谁不需要陪伴呢?
- Thank you for this. I needed the company.  - Who doesn't?

6
00:00:12,930 --> 00:00:14,460
我是来和你谈条件的
I'm here to make you an offer.

7
00:00:14,460 --> 00:00:17,200
如果你愿意来为我们工作 联邦调查局很愿意...
The Bureau is willing to drop all the charges against you...

8
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,760
- 撤销对你的一切指控  - 为联邦调查局工作?
- if you come and work for us.  - For the FBI?

9
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:22,800
我的条款 我要你读完之后
My terms. I need you to read them

10
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,060
签上名
and sign it.

11
00:00:24,060 --> 00:00:25,460
这些我们可以达成
We can work with this.

12
00:00:25,460 --> 00:00:27,560
我把我家里电话留给你...
I'm gonna give you my home phone number...

13
00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:30,430
说不定哪天你就回国了
in case you ever make it back to the States.

14
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:33,360
你现在脚踏美国的领土 我代表联邦政府
You are on U.S.soil now, I am the Federal Government,

15
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:35,560
告诉你 这...
and I am telling you that this...

16
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:37,400
才是协议
is the deal.

17
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:40,560
那不过是张餐巾 要么签 要么走
That is a napkin. Take it or leave it.

18
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,730
我走
I'll leave it.

19
00:00:42,730 --> 00:00:44,560
- Kim 是你?  - 是Fischer探员  
- Kim?  - Agent Fischer.

20
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,130
Fischer探员
Agent fischer.

21
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:52,130
华盛顿 Cannon River警局

22
00:01:09,600 --> 00:01:11,060
订书机去哪了?
Have you seen the stapler?

23
00:01:11,060 --> 00:01:12,500
昨天坏了
It busted yesterday.

24
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,130
- 我们只有一个吗?  - 呃...
- We have another one?  - Um...

25
00:01:14,130 --> 00:01:15,560
你可以用复印机
You know, maybe try the copying machine.

26
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:17,500
- 复印机也可以订的  - 那样会浪费纸吧? 
- It has a staple function.  - Isn't that a waste of paper?

27
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,000
不会 我们就纸最多
No, we have tons of paper.

28
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,700
我还是去找个回形针吧
I'm gonna go with a paper clip.

29
00:01:23,530 --> 00:01:24,660
Fischer探员
Agent Fischer.

30
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:26,830
Lisbon警长 我们能聊几句吗?
Chief Lisbon. Can we talk?

31
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,960
这好可爱啊
It's adorable.

32
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:33,200
请坐
Please. Sit down.

33
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,830
Jane还好吗?
How's Jane?

34
00:01:37,830 --> 00:01:39,330
他还在拘留
He is still in detention.

35
00:01:39,330 --> 00:01:40,630
我知道
I know.

36
00:01:40,630 --> 00:01:42,360
他们不送我的信
They won't deliver my letters.

37
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,630
都三个月了
Three months now.

38
00:01:43,630 --> 00:01:45,860
他被蓄意隔离了
He's being kept in isolation by design.

39
00:01:45,860 --> 00:01:47,400
蓄意?
By design?

40
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:49,800
你是说 除非他答应你们的要求
You mean until he does what you want.

41
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,160
- 我们想帮助他  - 你想利用他
- We want to help him out.  - You want to use him.

42
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,530
那样不好吗?
Is that so bad?

43
00:01:53,530 --> 00:01:55,030
你没有注意到吧
In case you haven't noticed,

44
00:01:55,030 --> 00:01:57,460
Jane就不是当联邦探员的料
Jane is hardly Federal Agent material.

45
00:01:57,460 --> 00:01:59,660
那他是加州探员的料?
Was he State Agent material?

46
00:01:59,660 --> 00:02:01,860
都不是 但至少他想在那儿工作
No, not really, but he wanted to be there.

47
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:04,560
他在加州调查局的时候 破了悬案十年的  
And while he was there, he stopped the 10-year reign

48
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,000
连环杀手案
of a mass murderer

49
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,430
并曝光了警界的腐败组织
and exposed a society of corruption in law enforcement.

50
00:02:08,430 --> 00:02:10,500
这事传遍了大江南北
That spread halfway across the country.

51
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:13,860
是啊 那些事情都出乎大家的意料 是吧?
Yeah, that didn't exactly go down by the books, did it?

52
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:16,530
没错 我们知道Jane的工作方式 也知道有风险 
Yeah, we know how Jane works. And we know he's a risk.

53
00:02:16,530 --> 00:02:18,730
但他也有好的一面
But we can't ignore the upside.

54
00:02:18,730 --> 00:02:21,400
他结了你接手的每个案子
He closed every case you were ever assigned.

55
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,630
没错 但他有帮手
Yeah, he had help.

56
00:02:22,630 --> 00:02:24,330
所以我今天到这来了
Which is why I'm here.

57
00:02:24,330 --> 00:02:26,400
你想要什么?
What do you want from me?

58
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,430
帮助我 Lisbon
Help me, Lisbon.

59
00:02:28,430 --> 00:02:30,660
国家安全出问题了
There are National Security issues at play.

60
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:33,460
Jane不和我们合作 除非我们满足他的要求
Jane won't work with us unless we meet his demands.

61
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:35,430
他太骄傲了 得挫挫锐气
He has too much pride to back down.

62
00:02:35,430 --> 00:02:38,160
你得让他赢 满足他的某项条件
You got to give him a win. Meet one of his demands.

63
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,660
他的某项条件就是你
One of his demands is you.

64
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:41,000
那就换一个吧
Meet another one.

65
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,900
我们没时间了
We're running out of time.

66
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:45,430
你就这么忙 以至于你都不能
Is your work here so pressing that you can't take a break

67
00:02:45,430 --> 00:02:46,830
帮帮自己的国家吗?
to help your country?

68
00:02:46,830 --> 00:02:50,000
警长 我用无线电通知了Phelps警员
Hey, Chief, uh, I radioed Officer Phelps.

69
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,900
他会去凯马特(美国零售公司)买一个新的订书机
He can run to Kmart for a new stapler.

70
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,230
要斯温格来恩的还是史丹利牌的?
Swingline or Stanley Bostitch?

71
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:01,230
德州 奥斯汀市 联邦调查局拘留所

72
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,130
稀客 太好了
Visitor. Splendid.

73
00:03:14,130 --> 00:03:17,100
看你这样子好像不情愿来啊
Not a willing one, based on the posture.

74
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,000
这样就好多了
That's a little better.

75
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:23,030
很高兴见到你
It's good to see you.

76
00:03:23,030 --> 00:03:24,430
感觉怎么样?
How you holding up?

77
00:03:24,430 --> 00:03:26,260
啊...
Ah...

78
00:03:26,260 --> 00:03:28,860
你懂被监禁的感觉的
You know what incarceration's like.

79
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:30,530
不太懂
Not really.

80
00:03:30,530 --> 00:03:32,130
没必要装 Lisbon 
Well, there's no need to pretend, Lisbon.

81
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:33,630
我们处境相同
We're both in the same predicament.

82
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:36,600
怎么会呢? 我自己有家 还有受人尊重的职业
How is that? I have a home and a respected career.

83
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,460
而你却因为谋杀被监禁了
You're locked up for murder.

84
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:40,830
你在吹毛求疵 我们都被困住了
Eh, you're splitting hairs. We're both trapped.

85
00:03:40,830 --> 00:03:42,660
我怎么就被困住了呢?
How am I trapped?

86
00:03:42,660 --> 00:03:44,130
因为你住在华盛顿
You live in Washington.

87
00:03:44,130 --> 00:03:45,430
我挺喜欢华盛顿的
I love Washington.

88
00:03:45,430 --> 00:03:46,500
说谎
High voice.

89
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,900
你为什么这么顽固?
Why are you being so stubborn?

90
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:54,230
联邦调查局已经答应你"不用蹲监狱"了
The FBI is offering you a "get out of jail free" card.

91
00:03:54,230 --> 00:03:56,760
- 听你说好像是件好事  - 不是好事吗? 
- Well, you make that sound like a good thing.  - Isn't it?

92
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,930
按照他们的条款 就不是
Not on their terms.

93
00:03:57,930 --> 00:03:59,660
如果他们不答应我的条件
If I can't live on my terms,

94
00:03:59,660 --> 00:04:01,800
我最终还是会蹲监狱
I'm in prison anyway.

95
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:04,630
待在这个拘留小套间也挺舒适的
Might as well just stay in this cozy little detention suite.

96
00:04:04,630 --> 00:04:06,600
行 你自己决定 但今天不行
Well, that's your call, but not today.

97
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,160
联邦调查局逼我来这
The FBI dragged me here,

98
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,630
除非你帮他们破那个案子
and they're not gonna let me go home

99
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:11,460
他们不会让我回家的
until you help them with a case.

100
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:14,260
所以快站起来 我们走
So get your ass out of the chair and let's go.

101
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,360
好样的...
Okay...

102
00:04:20,130 --> 00:04:22,400
联邦调查员
Federal officers coming through.

