00:05:01,030 --> 00:05:02,460
这边
Over here.

110
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:06,860
我们将会在这个案子上协助纽约警方
We'll be assisting our New York office on this case.

111
00:05:06,860 --> 00:05:10,830
我们的救星到了
And our asset has just arrived.

112
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:13,060
Jane先生 Lisbon 你们好
Mr. Jane. Lisbon.

113
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:15,400
你说我是救星 太令我感动了
You called me an asset. That's so touching.

114
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:17,330
我是一个乐天派
I'm an optimist.

115
00:05:17,330 --> 00:05:19,560
请坐 那我们继续说 
We just started briefing, if you'll have a seat.

116
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:21,600
- 好 嗨 Cho  - 嗨 Jane  
- I'm fine. Hey, Cho.  - Hey, Jane.

117
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,030
最近怎么样?
What's going on?

118
00:05:23,030 --> 00:05:24,530
我们正在开会
Hey.  We're in the middle of a briefing.

119
00:05:24,530 --> 00:05:28,130
- 一会聊吧  - 知道了 你好
- We can catch up later.  - Gotcha. Hey there.

120
00:05:31,930 --> 00:05:34,900
这是Abel Schneiderman
This is Abel Schneiderman.

121
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,400
他带领的团队编写了用于
He led the team that wrote the new source code

122
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,730
保护联邦储备银行系统的新源代码
to protect the Federal Reserve Banking System.

123
00:05:40,730 --> 00:05:44,600
两天前 他从他在布鲁克林的公寓里失踪
Two days ago, he disappeared from his loft in Brooklyn.

124
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,460
他的卧室里有争斗的痕迹
There were signs of a struggle in his bedroom.

125
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:50,260
Schneiderman的手机被摔在地下
Schneiderman's cell phone was busted on the floor.

126
00:05:50,260 --> 00:05:52,830
我们猜测他被绑架了
We are working on the theory that he has been kidnapped.

127
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,330
有人要赎金了吗?
Has there been a ransom demand?

128
00:05:54,330 --> 00:05:56,200
目前还没有 但我们觉得会有
Not yet, but we're expecting it.

129
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,930
他们或者是想要赎金 或者是索要代码
Well, it's either that, or they will break him for the code

130
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:00,260
去击溃
and launch an attack

131
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:02,000
美联储电脑系统
on the Federal Reserve Computer System.

132
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,560
Abel所知道的能让我们的银行系统
What Abel knows could bring our banking system

133
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,200
彻底瘫痪
to its knees.

134
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:08,300
这太有意思了
Oh. This is exciting.

135
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:09,600
这是我要处理的案子吗?
Is this the case that I'm here for?

136
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,860
我们等你很久了
We're getting to you.

137
00:06:10,860 --> 00:06:12,360
我就知道你看见我了 对吧?
I knew you saw me. Huh?

138
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,860
我就知道
I knew it.

139
00:06:14,860 --> 00:06:16,360
Abel有个年轻的妻子...
Abel has a young wife...

140
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,000
叫Defiance Schneiderman
Defiance Schneiderman.

141
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,200
不难看出 她情绪很激动
Now understandably, she's emotional

142
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:23,330
而且认定联邦调查局
and believes that the FBI is not utilizing

143
00:06:23,330 --> 00:06:25,700
没有倾其所有去找她丈夫
all of its resources to find her husband.

144
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:28,100
更糟的是 我们还不能让联邦调查局以外的人知道
And unfortunately, we can't let anyone outside the FBI

145
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:30,760
Schneiderman先生被绑架了
know that Mr. Schneiderman's been kidnapped.

146
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,130
否则金融系统就会受到重创
Otherwise, it could cripple the financial systems.

147
00:06:33,130 --> 00:06:34,830
纽约当局派了联邦调查局探员
The New York Office sent a FBI Agent

148
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:37,000
假扮成灵媒 
posing as a psychic,

149
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,460
但Schneiderman女士一眼就识破了
but Ms. Schneiderman saw right through that.

150
00:06:39,460 --> 00:06:41,660
当然了 她是吉普赛人
Well, of course. She's a gypsy.

151
00:06:41,660 --> 00:06:44,460
吉普赛女人都多少了解些通灵的事
Woman knows a thing or two about psychics.

152
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:45,660
那你为什么要说她是吉普赛人?
What makes you say gypsy?

153
00:06:45,660 --> 00:06:47,300
Defiance是个吉普赛人的名字
Well, Defiance is a gypsy name.

154
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:48,560
你看她的卧室
Look at her bedroom.

155
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:51,000
那是吉普赛猫薄荷
It's gypsy catnip.

156
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,800
Abel是犹太人 那就说明
Abel there is Jewish, which means

157
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,960
她背弃了自己的宗教结的婚
she turned her back on her entire clan to get married.

158
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:57,260
而现在她既找不到丈夫 也毫无家庭支援
Now she has a missing husband and no family for support.

159
00:06:57,260 --> 00:06:59,500
所以才会想找灵媒帮忙
It's a psychic 9-1-1.

160
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:03,100
这就是我们现在了解到的情况
Well... there we are.

161
00:07:03,100 --> 00:07:04,430
开始行动吧
Let's go to work.

162
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:06,430
奥斯汀国际机场

163
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,100
谢谢
Thank you.

164
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,360
经济舱 我还想着坐联邦喷气式飞机呢
Coach. I was expecting a federal jet,

165
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,530
或者至少也得是直升机吧
or at least a helicopter.

166
00:07:21,530 --> 00:07:22,730
我要坐靠近走道的位置
Call the aisle seat.

167
00:07:22,730 --> 00:07:24,760
你要按照上面说的坐
You'll sit where you're told.

168
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:26,760
别紧张
You know, you can relax.

169
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:27,830
没事
Everything's good.

170
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:30,160
你还是一个联邦囚犯呢
You're still a Federal detainee,

171
00:07:30,160 --> 00:07:32,430
并受我监管 所以我不会掉以轻心的
and you're in my charge, so, no, I won't relax.

172
00:07:32,430 --> 00:07:35,360
照我说的做 明白吗?
And you'll do as I tell you, you understand?

173
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:37,030
我知道 Kim
Oh, I understand you, Kim.

174
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:40,100
我很了解你... 比你自己都了解你
I understand you very well... better than you do yourself.

175
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,960
你要待在联邦调查局成员的
You will stay within arm's length

176
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:45,730
一臂范围之内
of FBI personnel at all times.

177
