But he's not answering my phone calls.

247
00:11:08,130 --> 00:11:10,730
这很奇怪
Hmm. That is odd.

248
00:11:10,730 --> 00:11:13,130
你能找到他吗? 你能找到Abel吗?
Can you find him? Can you find Abel?

249
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:14,930
你最后一次见他是在哪?
Where was the last place you saw him?

250
00:11:14,930 --> 00:11:17,230
是前天晚上在屋顶上
On the roof, night before last.

251
00:11:17,230 --> 00:11:18,730
你们在屋顶干什么?
What were you doing up there?

252
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:22,230
和女友们喝杯酒
Sharing a bottle of wine with my girlfriends.

253
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,830
Abel带着笔记本电脑上来了
Abel came up there with his laptop.

254
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:28,100
他喜欢在屋顶上放松 那里非常祥和
He likes to unwind on the roof. It's peaceful.

255
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:31,660
我想去看看屋顶
I'd like to take a look at this roof.

256
00:11:35,800 --> 00:11:38,960
门廊尽头的台阶就是
It's the stairs at the end of the hallway.

257
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,130
嗨
Hi.

258
00:11:43,130 --> 00:11:44,830
你干嘛?
What are you doing?

259
00:11:44,830 --> 00:11:46,960
猫眼后面有人
Spyhole went dark.

260
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:52,860
什么?
What?

261
00:11:52,860 --> 00:11:54,830
我们是联邦调查局的
We're with the FBI.

262
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:56,660
先生 在过去几周内
Sir, did you see or hear anything unusual

263
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:58,230
你有没有看到或听到不寻常的动静?
in the last couple weeks?

264
00:11:58,230 --> 00:11:59,860
我早就告诉过你们了 没有
I already told you people, no.

265
00:11:59,860 --> 00:12:01,200
我们是另一个部门的
We're with a different office.

266
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:04,730
多得像蟑螂一样
So many, like roaches.

267
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:07,960
人很随和
Nice guy.

268
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:10,430
他叫Nguyen Hai 是越南难民
His name is Nguyen Hai. He's a Vietnamese refugee.

269
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:13,230
过去经营一家面馆 现在这房子是他的
He used to run a noodle shop. Now he owns the building.

270
00:12:13,230 --> 00:12:14,900
失踪那晚他在家
He was home the evening of the disappearance,

271
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:16,400
但他什么都没听到或看到
but he didn't hear or see anything.

272
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,900
你怎么知道的?
How do you know that?

273
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:19,630
我读过卷宗了
I read the case files.

274
00:12:19,630 --> 00:12:21,360
我以为你对这案子不感兴趣
I thought you weren't interested in the case.

275
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,160
飞机上很无聊
It was a long plane ride.

276
00:12:31,260 --> 00:12:34,130
如果Abel消失那晚是在楼顶
So if Abel came up here the night he disappeared,

277
00:12:34,130 --> 00:12:36,060
为什么卧室是乱的?
why was the bedroom trashed?

278
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:39,600
我不知道 我从酒吧回来很晚
I don't know. I got home late from the bar.

279
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:42,930
进来的时候 Abel不见了 房间里一团糟
When I got in, Abel was gone, and our room was wrecked.

280
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:45,230
他在等人吗?
Was he expecting any visitors?

281
00:12:45,230 --> 00:12:47,830
应该没有
I don't think so.

282
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:50,330
否则我走之前他会告诉我的
He would have told me before I left.

283
00:12:50,330 --> 00:12:52,330
这是你丈夫的花园
This is your husband's garden.

284
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:57,000
没错 你怎么知道?
Yeah. How'd you know?

285
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,530
他的能量在这
His energy's here.

286
00:12:59,530 --> 00:13:01,700
他把自己的能量倾注在这座花园里
He pours his energy into this garden

287
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,860
因为他不喜欢做电脑程序员
because he doesn't like being a computer programmer.

288
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:05,100
没错
That's right.

289
00:13:05,100 --> 00:13:07,200
他在那个世界里感觉被束缚了
He feels trapped in that world.

290
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,730
是的
Yes.

291
00:13:09,730 --> 00:13:11,230
那是个秩序井然的世界
It's an orderly world,

292
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:13,700
充满规则和数字
full of rules and numbers.

293
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:15,460
但那不是Abel的世界
But it's not Abel's world.

294
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:17,960
他将自己视作叛逆者
He sees himself more as a rebel soul.

295
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,200
他真的很喜欢切·格瓦拉
He really loves that Che Guevara guy.

296
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:23,560
所以他才骑摩托车
Yeah, that's why he rides a motorcycle.

297
00:13:23,560 --> 00:13:26,100
自己种蔬菜
Grows his own vegetables.

298
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:28,060
所以他才和你结婚
That's why he married you.

299
00:13:28,060 --> 00:13:29,600
就因为我是吉普赛人?
Oh, because I'm a Gypsy?

300
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:31,430
是啊
Yeah.

301
00:13:31,430 --> 00:13:33,430
因为你有勇气为爱
Because you had the courage to walk away from

302
00:13:33,430 --> 00:13:36,800
离开几个世纪以来的传统
centuries of tradition for love.

303
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:38,560
你或许不知道 但你给了你丈夫
You may not know it, but you give your husband

304
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:41,660
做自己的内在勇气
the courage to be who he is on the inside.

305
00:13:41,660 --> 00:13:43,860
Abel还活着吗?
Is Abel alive?

306
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,400
你何不帮我找到他呢?
Why don't you help me find him?

307
